</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,152,458]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,391,417]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is a brachypterous, flightless species. The elytra are fused along the suture, and the vestigial wings are about 1/2 as long as the elytra.
</paragraph>
